54:28.799 --> 54:31.678
- Maxton, are you okay?

54:31.702 --> 54:34.305
Come on guys, let's help him.

55:12.577 --> 55:14.044
- You did amazing.

55:15.613 --> 55:17.791
Is your leg gonna
be okay, though?

55:17.815 --> 55:19.526
- Oh yeah, I think so.

55:19.550 --> 55:21.528
I think it's probably
just bruised or sprained.

55:21.552 --> 55:23.730
I'll put some ice on
it when I get home.

55:23.754 --> 55:24.965
- Oh, hey, let me help you.

55:24.989 --> 55:25.989
- Oh, thanks.

55:27.625 --> 55:32.630
- So, besides the injury,
are you always that good?

55:34.599 --> 55:35.509
- You know what?

55:35.533 --> 55:38.469
Today I think I had
some extra motivation.

55:40.671 --> 55:43.717
Thank you for coming,
watching me play.

55:43.741 --> 55:44.951
It means a lot.

55:44.975 --> 55:46.620
- Of course.

55:46.644 --> 55:50.991
- You know, it's funny,
I've always liked you

55:51.015 --> 55:53.551
but I never never thought
I'd feel like this.

55:55.185 --> 55:56.185
I like this.

55:56.954 --> 55:57.954
I like us.

56:08.833 --> 56:12.002
- Come on, let's go get
some ice on your leg.

56:26.717 --> 56:28.385
Oh, it's you.

56:29.119 --> 56:30.119
- Nice welcome.

56:30.688 --> 56:32.466
So you back from
the soccer game?

56:32.490 --> 56:34.435
- Yeah, just barely.

56:34.459 --> 56:35.201
- How was it?

56:35.225 --> 56:37.003
Did Clarise get mad?

56:37.027 --> 56:40.707
- I actually don't think she
remembered I went to go study.

56:40.731 --> 56:43.176
I snuck in through the side
door so nobody would see me.

56:43.200 --> 56:44.802
- Indy, get down here!

56:45.870 --> 56:49.149
- Oh, sorry I have to go.

56:49.173 --> 56:50.684
Clarise is calling.

56:50.708 --> 56:52.653
- Calling or yelling?

56:52.677 --> 56:53.878
- Yeah, bye.

56:59.550 --> 57:00.550
- Have a seat.

57:03.187 --> 57:06.166
So would you like to tell us
where you really were today?

57:06.190 --> 57:07.825
And don't lie.

57:09.259 --> 57:11.672
- I was at Maxton's soccer game.

57:11.696 --> 57:15.542
- So you weren't
studying after all.

57:15.566 --> 57:16.634
And what about after?

57:18.235 --> 57:19.813
- After?

57:19.837 --> 57:21.782
I came straight home after.

57:21.806 --> 57:22.949
- Really?

57:22.973 --> 57:25.619
Because Clarise received
a call that would

57:25.643 --> 57:27.044
seem to imply otherwise.

57:28.546 --> 57:30.924
- Mrs. Whitman called
me and said that

57:30.948 --> 57:33.627
she saw you and
some boy making out

57:33.651 --> 57:34.895
in the middle of
the soccer field

57:34.919 --> 57:36.854
right there in front
of everyone to see.

57:37.822 --> 57:39.199
- What?

57:39.223 --> 57:42.536
We kissed once but I promise
we didn't make out.

57:42.560 --> 57:46.740
- Do you have any idea
how embarrassing it is

57:46.764 --> 57:49.242
to receive a call like that?

57:49.266 --> 57:50.266
- I'm sorry.

57:51.669 --> 57:53.580
- I have to go into my office.

57:53.604 --> 57:56.983
Do whatever you need
to do here, Clarise.

57:57.007 --> 57:57.818
Deal with her.

57:57.842 --> 57:59.553
- What?

57:59.577 --> 58:01.522
You're not leaving me here
to handle this by myself.

58:01.546 --> 58:02.756
What, do you want
her going around

58:02.780 --> 58:05.559
the neighborhood
like some floozy?

58:05.583 --> 58:08.729
- Well, with her mother what
would we really expect?

58:08.753 --> 58:10.163
- What's that supposed to mean?

58:10.187 --> 58:11.598
- Fix this.

58:11.622 --> 58:12.799
- No.

58:12.823 --> 58:14.383
Do you have something
you'd like to say?

58:15.593 --> 58:20.064
My actions, my
choices, are mine.

58:21.198 --> 58:24.201
So don't you dare pin
this on my mother.

58:25.570 --> 58:28.749
My mom loved me and cared for me

58:28.773 --> 58:32.853
and worked herself sick
trying to provide for me

58:32.877 --> 58:36.056
and she had nothing but nice
things to say about you two

58:36.080 --> 58:41.085
so I am done hearing how
awful you think she was.

58:41.819 --> 58:43.597
- You don't get to...

58:43.621 --> 58:47.000
- I know you don't want me.

58:47.024 --> 58:50.737
I knew it the moment I
showed up to stay with you.

58:50.761 --> 58:53.774
I was just some poor
relative who was coming

58:53.798 --> 58:58.803
to intrude on your lives but
I was loved before this

58:59.837 --> 59:01.772
and I know the
difference between this

59:02.973 --> 59:06.010
and what a real family is
supposed to feel like.

59:07.612 --> 59:11.682
I have done everything you have
asked me to do, everything,

59:13.250 --> 59:15.319
and it is sill not enough.

59:17.287 --> 59:20.601
Sure, Jayda and Kaitlyn
get to go on dates

59:20.625 --> 59:24.795
and see their friends
and have normal lives

59:27.064 --> 59:28.064
but not me.

59:29.299 --> 59:33.203
What is it going to take for
you to see me as family?

59:37.041 --> 59:41.922
- Oh, oh, missy, how
entertaining was that?

59:44.348 --> 59:45.750
- I'm serious.

59:46.651 --> 59:47.718
- You want serious?

59:48.819 --> 59:52.766
If you don't learn to respect
both of us in this home

59:52.790 --> 59:55.793
you can find another
place to stay.

59:59.864 --> 01:00:04.010
- And what is respect
to you, Uncle David?

01:00:04.034 --> 01:00:06.112
Doing all the chores?

01:00:06.136 --> 01:00:10.083
Staying away during
family events?

01:00:10.107 --> 01:00:14.054
Living in the attic and not
having a life outside of school

01:00:14.078 --> 01:00:18.859
until you tell me to come
make dinner for you?

01:00:18.883 --> 01:00:19.884
Is that respect?

01:00:21.251 --> 01:00:24.865
Because if so, what of that
have I not been doing?

01:00:24.889 --> 01:00:28.368
- You're acting as if we're
treating you like a maid.

01:00:28.392 --> 01:00:32.739
Oh, after everything
that we did after all

01:00:32.763 --> 01:00:36.701
the things we changed to make
room for you in our lives.

01:00:38.035 --> 01:00:40.080
- Do you hear yourself?

01:00:40.104 --> 01:00:41.347
- Enough.

01:00:41.371 --> 01:00:44.150
You will go to your room and we

01:00:44.174 --> 01:00:46.319
will decide on a
punishment for you,

01:00:46.343 --> 01:00:49.790
you selfish little brat.
- David!

01:00:49.814 --> 01:00:52.349
- And let me tell you,
it will be severe.

01:00:55.920 --> 01:00:56.920
Go now.

01:02:25.542 --> 01:02:27.888
- Hey, Indy, I can't
really talk right now.

01:02:27.912 --> 01:02:30.056
- Sorry, did I wake you up?

01:02:30.080 --> 01:02:31.291
- No, no, it's okay.

01:02:31.315 --> 01:02:33.794
It's just my ankle,
my mom made me go

01:02:33.818 --> 01:02:36.229
to the clinic to get an x-ray.

01:02:36.253 --> 01:02:37.898
- Are you okay?

01:02:37.922 --> 01:02:40.867
- Yeah, I should be, I'm
just still in a lot of pain.

01:02:40.891 --> 01:02:41.992
Can I call you back?

01:02:42.893 --> 01:02:43.894
- Um.

01:02:45.996 --> 01:02:47.798
I'm having a really rough night.

01:02:50.500 --> 01:02:51.500
It's bad here.

01:02:52.402 --> 01:02:53.814
- Yeah?

01:02:53.838 --> 01:02:56.917
- It's probably the
worst it's ever been.

01:02:56.941 --> 01:02:58.985
- I'm sorry, maybe
just give your aunt

01:02:59.009 --> 01:03:00.220
some time to cool down?

01:03:00.244 --> 01:03:01.545
That usually works, right?

01:03:04.348 --> 01:03:05.348
- I'm scared.

01:03:06.516 --> 01:03:07.861
- Oh, hey, the doctor
just came back in

01:03:07.885 --> 01:03:09.930
so can I call you back tomorrow?

01:03:09.954 --> 01:03:10.954
- Tomorrow?

01:03:11.488 --> 01:03:12.966
Yeah, sure.

01:03:12.990 --> 01:03:14.558
- Okay, uh, night.

01:03:52.997 --> 01:03:54.640
- Wait a minute.

01:03:54.664 --> 01:03:55.664
Are you leaving?

01:03:59.169 --> 01:04:00.837
Indy, what's going on?

01:04:02.272 --> 01:04:07.087
- I missed up really really bad.

01:04:07.111 --> 01:04:08.212
- Okay, what happened?

01:04:09.679 --> 01:04:12.125
- Guess one of the neighbors
called Clarise and told her

01:04:12.149 --> 01:04:14.351
I was making out with
Maxton at his soccer game.

01:04:15.219 --> 01:04:17.287
- Uh, were you?

01:04:19.323 --> 01:04:21.534
Sorry, that's not important.

01:04:21.558 --> 01:04:24.137
- We kissed, we didn't
make out, though.

01:04:24.161 --> 01:04:26.030
It was in front of
a group of people.

01:04:27.564 --> 01:04:29.333
- And your aunt chewed you out?

01:04:30.935 --> 01:04:31.935
- Her and David.

01:04:32.970 --> 01:04:34.414
And then David made a comment
about how he thought

01:04:34.438 --> 01:04:38.142
my mom raised me poorly
and I just lost it.

01:04:39.109 --> 01:04:42.112
All the stuff I had
pent up just came out.

01:04:43.080 --> 01:04:45.158
And then David said
that if I disrespected

01:04:45.182 --> 01:04:46.326
them one more time
I'd be kicked out

01:04:46.350 --> 01:04:49.395
and then he said my punishment
was gonna be really bad.

01:04:49.419 --> 01:04:52.098
- So you came upstairs
and started packing.

01:04:52.122 --> 01:04:53.157
- Yeah.

01:04:54.724 --> 01:04:57.670
- Did you tell him how unfair
it was that you're the maid

01:04:57.694 --> 01:05:00.006
and the cook and the
prisoner all while

01:05:00.030 --> 01:05:02.008
they get to go out and live?

01:05:02.032 --> 01:05:03.443
- Sort of.

01:05:03.467 --> 01:05:05.645
Look, it was awful.

01:05:05.669 --> 01:05:08.414
My filter was completely gone.

01:05:08.438 --> 01:05:09.438
- So now what?

01:05:11.375 --> 01:05:13.143
- I don't know.

01:05:15.012 --> 01:05:16.313
- Do you need a place to stay?

01:05:19.984 --> 01:05:21.285
- No, I'll be fine.

01:05:22.452 --> 01:05:24.421
- Their threats aren't
going to get any better.

01:05:25.589 --> 01:05:26.766
Look, my dad's a family
therapist and he sees

01:05:26.790 --> 01:05:29.635
this stuff all the time, and the
problem with abusive people

01:05:29.659 --> 01:05:32.096
is that they just always
think they're right.

01:05:33.330 --> 01:05:34.931
- You think they're abusive?

01:05:35.699 --> 01:05:36.699
- Yeah.

01:05:38.168 --> 01:05:41.405
Their daughters are perfect
and you're not allowed to be.

01:05:43.207 --> 01:05:46.043
Excuses to keep you grounded,
not inviting you to things,

01:05:47.211 --> 01:05:48.651
not even giving you
a proper bedroom.

01:05:50.014 --> 01:05:52.125
The list goes on and on.

01:05:52.149 --> 01:05:56.396
- I mean it's bad
but it's not abuse.

01:05:56.420 --> 01:05:57.420
- Yes it is.

01:05:58.522 --> 01:06:00.166
It's definitely emotional
abuse which can be

01:06:00.190 --> 01:06:01.992
so harmful and dangerous.

01:06:05.195 --> 01:06:08.108
Look, I think that you
need to come with me.

01:06:08.132 --> 01:06:10.667
- Can I have time to
think about this?

01:06:11.801 --> 01:06:15.215
- Actually, do you
mind if I call my dad

01:06:15.239 --> 01:06:16.640
and just ask for his advice?

01:06:19.809 --> 01:06:21.321
I'll just be a second
but in the meantime

01:06:21.345 --> 01:06:23.547
you should really really
keep packing, okay?

01:06:32.656 --> 01:06:33.657
Yeah, I'll tell her.

01:06:35.259 --> 01:06:36.259
Okay.

01:06:36.760 --> 01:06:37.760
Bye.

01:06:39.363 --> 01:06:41.041
- What'd he say?

01:06:41.065 --> 01:06:43.400
- Well, he was obviously
concerned when I told him.

01:06:45.069 --> 01:06:47.680
What I didn't know is now
that I've told him by law

01:06:47.704 --> 01:06:51.675
he's gotta tell child
protective services.

01:06:53.310 --> 01:06:54.310
- What?

01:06:55.445 --> 01:06:56.480
Are you sure?

01:06:59.416 --> 01:07:01.594
- Indy, he could lose his
license if he didn't.

01:07:01.618 --> 01:07:03.329
- This is insane.

01:07:03.353 --> 01:07:05.522
- I know, but, look, I'm sorry

01:07:06.656 --> 01:07:09.135
and I promise we'll
keep it private.

01:07:09.159 --> 01:07:10.594
- Bryant, I can't do this.

01:07:11.495 --> 01:07:12.605
Jayda and Kaitlyn...

01:07:12.629 --> 01:07:14.298
- No, this is not about them.

01:07:15.299 --> 01:07:16.299
This is about you.

01:07:18.202 --> 01:07:20.613
My dad says that you
can come stay with us.

01:07:20.637 --> 01:07:22.315
He's certified to
take in foster kids

01:07:22.339 --> 01:07:25.175
and he really doesn't
think you're safe here.

01:07:26.843 --> 01:07:28.588
Look, I think that
you just need to

01:07:28.612 --> 01:07:29.655
come to stay with us tonight.

01:07:29.679 --> 01:07:31.391
- I really don't think that

01:07:31.415 --> 01:07:32.858
they're gonna hit
me or anything.

01:07:32.882 --> 01:07:34.260
- No, but they might just lock

01:07:34.284 --> 01:07:35.161
you in your room or something.

01:07:35.185 --> 01:07:36.786
- They always do that.

01:07:38.555 --> 01:07:40.233
What, is that
considered abuse, too?

01:07:40.257 --> 01:07:42.302
- I'm getting the
bags, we're leaving.

01:07:42.326 --> 01:07:43.703
- You didn't answer my question.

01:07:43.727 --> 01:07:44.727
- I don't need to.

01:07:45.795 --> 01:07:47.407
If they're going to
lock you in your room

01:07:47.431 --> 01:07:49.575
for being a normal child,
imagine what they're gonna

01:07:49.599 --> 01:07:51.101
do when they're all upset.

01:07:54.404 --> 01:07:55.404
We're leaving.

01:08:04.848 --> 01:08:05.791
- Hey, come on in.

01:08:05.815 --> 01:08:06.815
Welcome, Indy.

01:08:08.218 --> 01:08:09.218
- Thank you.

01:08:10.154 --> 01:08:11.264
Your home is beautiful.

01:08:11.288 --> 01:08:13.089
- Oh, listen.

01:08:14.258 --> 01:08:16.902
I want you to feel as
comfortable here as you can

01:08:16.926 --> 01:08:20.305
so I hope you don't mind that
your room is next to Bryant's.

01:08:20.330 --> 01:08:24.768
He is a boy and they, you
know, they stink sometimes.

01:08:26.336 --> 01:08:28.648
And I know you're really tired
but if you feel up to it

01:08:28.671 --> 01:08:31.216
would you mind answering
some questions for me?

01:08:31.241 --> 01:08:33.843
It'll help me know better
what to do in the morning.

01:08:35.578 --> 01:08:37.256
Yeah?

01:08:37.281 --> 01:08:39.325
Okay, and then Bryant will
help you get settled after.

01:08:39.349 --> 01:08:40.550
Okay, just through here.

01:08:50.727 --> 01:08:52.562
Now just get some
rest for now, Indy.

01:08:53.430 --> 01:08:54.840
- I will.

01:08:54.863 --> 01:08:56.633
And thank you for...

01:08:57.667 --> 01:08:59.269
- Oh, we are happy to.

01:09:00.770 --> 01:09:03.216
Bryant, could you
show her to her room?

01:09:03.240 --> 01:09:05.274
- Come on, you can meet my
sisters in the morning.

01:09:12.982 --> 01:09:14.149
- Here's your room.

01:09:15.519 --> 01:09:16.429
- Thanks.

01:09:16.453 --> 01:09:17.554
- Yep.

01:09:22.725 --> 01:09:24.304
- What do you think
Clarise is gonna do

01:09:24.328 --> 01:09:25.871
when she realizes I'm not there?

01:09:25.895 --> 01:09:27.439
- Don't worry about them.

01:09:27.464 --> 01:09:29.475
Will you focus on
yourself for once?

01:09:29.499 --> 01:09:32.345
- I just really hope I
did the right thing.

01:09:32.368 --> 01:09:34.314
- You did do the right thing.

01:09:34.337 --> 01:09:36.706
Besides, you're
here with friends.

01:09:37.941 --> 01:09:38.941
- Okay.

01:09:39.975 --> 01:09:41.421
- All right, and if
you can't fall asleep

01:09:41.444 --> 01:09:43.356
just shoot me a text, kay?

01:09:43.380 --> 01:09:45.540
We'll go watch a movie in the
living room or something.

01:09:52.721 --> 01:09:53.721
- Thank you.

01:09:55.825 --> 01:09:56.825
For everything.

01:09:57.961 --> 01:10:00.364
- How did we get to this point?

01:10:01.398 --> 01:10:02.775
- You killed my cat.

01:10:05.469 --> 01:10:07.480
- And I'll never live that down.

01:10:07.504 --> 01:10:08.504
Ever.

01:10:09.373 --> 01:10:10.373
- Nope.

01:10:20.484 --> 01:10:21.485
- Goodnight.

01:11:01.425 --> 01:11:02.868
- Hey.

01:11:02.892 --> 01:11:04.570
- Ease up, save some
for everyone else.

01:11:04.594 --> 01:11:08.474
- It's good.

01:11:08.498 --> 01:11:09.909
- Morning.

01:11:09.933 --> 01:11:10.933
- Oh, hey.

01:11:12.736 --> 01:11:14.013
Indy these are my sisters.

01:11:14.037 --> 01:11:15.715
This is MacKenzie and Roni.

01:11:15.739 --> 01:11:17.717
I'm sure you know
MacKenzie from school.

01:11:17.741 --> 01:11:19.519
- We're glad you
could stay with us.

01:11:19.543 --> 01:11:21.645
I'm sorry the circumstances
aren't better.

01:11:22.812 --> 01:11:25.358
- I'm sorry I woke
up so late, I...

01:11:25.382 --> 01:11:27.393
- No worries, it's Sunday.

01:11:27.417 --> 01:11:28.417
- These are good.

01:11:30.620 --> 01:11:31.821
Indy, do you want syrup?

01:11:34.724 --> 01:11:35.724
- Those are for me?

01:11:36.893 --> 01:11:37.893
- Yeah.

01:11:40.564 --> 01:11:42.466
- Um, yeah, tons.

01:11:43.767 --> 01:11:44.834
- Have a seat.

01:11:46.436 --> 01:11:47.647
- Well, I hope we don't have

01:11:47.671 --> 01:11:50.583
any fist fights over
whipped cream this time.

01:11:50.607 --> 01:11:53.677
- I used up the last
of it yesterday.

01:11:54.844 --> 01:11:56.822
- Oh, well that settles that.

01:11:56.846 --> 01:11:59.392
So you had a chance to
meet the rest of the gang?

01:11:59.416 --> 01:12:03.629
- Yeah, and thank you guys so
much for letting me stay here.

01:12:03.653 --> 01:12:05.097
- Oh.

01:12:05.121 --> 01:12:06.699
Oh, you know, I've been on the
phone already this morning

01:12:06.723 --> 01:12:08.592
and things are moving forward.

01:12:09.526 --> 01:12:10.503
I'll tell you more
about it after you've

01:12:10.527 --> 01:12:11.595
had a chance to eat.

01:12:13.763 --> 01:12:15.408
Oh, you know, I've
been thinking.

01:12:15.432 --> 01:12:18.478
You know, we have that apartment
in the pool house out back,

01:12:18.502 --> 01:12:21.514
maybe you'd be more comfortable
staying out there.

01:12:21.538 --> 01:12:23.583
You know, you'd be
close to the family

01:12:23.607 --> 01:12:26.719
and to the house here but you'd
have a little privacy, too.

01:12:26.743 --> 01:12:29.522
- Um, yeah, that's fine.

01:12:30.980 --> 01:12:31.980
- Excuse me.

01:12:34.751 --> 01:12:35.751
- Eat up.

01:12:38.154 --> 01:12:40.099
- Hi, you wanna come in?

01:12:40.123 --> 01:12:41.567
- We need to take
Indy to her aunt

01:12:41.591 --> 01:12:42.735
and uncle's house
for an interview.

01:12:42.759 --> 01:12:45.170
- That is highly unusual.

01:12:45.194 --> 01:12:46.639
- They've hired a
powerful attorney

01:12:46.663 --> 01:12:48.908
and he's assisting
that the venue be

01:12:48.932 --> 01:12:50.643
the aunt and uncle's home.

01:12:50.667 --> 01:12:52.712
- No way, you are the
government representative

01:12:52.736 --> 01:12:54.414
you're supposed to
be keeping her safe.

01:12:54.438 --> 01:12:56.416
We are supposed
to keep her safe.

01:12:56.440 --> 01:12:57.149
- You know these things

01:12:57.173 --> 01:12:59.151
take time and some finagling.

01:12:59.175 --> 01:13:00.252
They are the legal guardians...

01:13:00.276 --> 01:13:02.555
- So you want her to go
back over there right now

01:13:02.579 --> 01:13:04.657
and face them after everything
she's been through?

01:13:04.681 --> 01:13:07.860
- We don't know what she's been
through, that's the point.

01:13:07.884 --> 01:13:10.496
But Officer Reid and I are
here to make sure she's safe.

01:13:10.520 --> 01:13:11.797
- Yeah, that or to force

01:13:11.821 --> 01:13:14.567
her back to her aunt's house.

01:13:14.591 --> 01:13:16.993
- Dr. Bailey, please
work with me here.

01:13:19.963 --> 01:13:21.006
- Indy?

01:13:21.030 --> 01:13:22.642
- How many pancakes did you eat?

01:13:22.666 --> 01:13:23.809
- A lot.

01:13:23.833 --> 01:13:24.644
Indy.

01:13:24.668 --> 01:13:25.945
- What's wrong?

01:13:30.674 --> 01:13:31.674
What's going on?

01:13:36.613 --> 01:13:37.647
Indy!

01:14:17.020 --> 01:14:18.555
- Was this all a joke?

01:14:19.589 --> 01:14:20.589
- What?

01:14:21.157 --> 01:14:23.068
- The whole saving me thing.

01:14:23.092 --> 01:14:24.092
- No.

01:14:25.261 --> 01:14:26.672
- I trusted you.

01:14:26.696 --> 01:14:28.131
- Hey, you're not going back.

01:14:29.265 --> 01:14:31.067
- I heard them
talking, they said

01:14:32.536 --> 01:14:33.479
there was a police officer

01:14:33.503 --> 01:14:35.715
there and they were saying
- Hey, hey, hey.

01:14:35.739 --> 01:14:36.749
Hey, hey, hey.

01:14:36.773 --> 01:14:38.117
Can I just explain?

01:14:38.141 --> 01:14:39.141
Please?

01:14:45.148 --> 01:14:46.559
Your aunt and uncle are trying

01:14:46.583 --> 01:14:48.861
all sorts of excuses
and tactics.

01:14:48.885 --> 01:14:51.597
Some that my dad have already
dealt with this morning.

01:14:51.621 --> 01:14:53.957
They're moving fast
but there are rules

01:14:55.659 --> 01:14:57.770
and you are not
going back there.

01:14:57.794 --> 01:15:01.598
- But I heard them talking.

01:15:03.833 --> 01:15:06.712
- Yeah, they were trying to
get you to do the interview

01:15:06.736 --> 01:15:08.681
at Clarise's house with
Child Protective Services

01:15:08.705 --> 01:15:11.174
but my dad is dead
set against that.

01:15:12.275 --> 01:15:13.786
You should not have
to be anywhere

01:15:13.810 --> 01:15:15.545
where you're feeling
uncomfortable.

01:15:16.980 --> 01:15:18.691
- Interview?

01:15:18.715 --> 01:15:21.160
- Yeah, look, you're
old enough to voice

01:15:21.184 --> 01:15:23.729
your own opinion now
so my dad talked to

01:15:23.753 --> 01:15:25.731
the Child Protective
Services lady

01:15:25.755 --> 01:15:28.224
and they agreed to let you
do it wherever you choose.

01:15:29.893 --> 01:15:34.530
- But why was there a
police officer there?

01:15:35.765 --> 01:15:37.643
- That was just a
precaution, you know,

01:15:37.667 --> 01:15:39.078
in case you had to go
back to your aunt's house

01:15:39.102 --> 01:15:40.804
they just wanted
you to feel safe.

01:15:46.275 --> 01:15:47.877
- Why are you doing this for me?

01:15:49.879 --> 01:15:50.879
- Why wouldn't we?

01:15:53.683 --> 01:15:55.961
Indy, I'm not gonna
sit there and watch

01:15:55.985 --> 01:15:59.022
you be treated horribly
and neither is my dad.

01:16:00.990 --> 01:16:02.768
- I don't wanna be a burden.

01:16:02.792 --> 01:16:03.936
- You're not a burden.

01:16:03.960 --> 01:16:08.297
- I just feel like I've been
causing a lot of problems.

01:16:10.734 --> 01:16:15.739
Your dad mentioned moving me
out to the pool house and I...

01:16:17.807 --> 01:16:20.143
- You got banished to the
attic in Clarise's house.

01:16:21.978 --> 01:16:24.748
Indy, that is not what
we meant by that.

01:16:26.249 --> 01:16:28.160
My dad just thought
you might want

01:16:28.184 --> 01:16:30.053
some privacy or personal space.

01:16:31.788 --> 01:16:33.833
Look, you are more than
welcome to stay in the house.

01:16:33.857 --> 01:16:36.769
Man, I'm sorry, we
should've thought of that.

01:16:36.793 --> 01:16:40.329
- No, I'm sorry
for overreacting.

01:16:41.865 --> 01:16:42.899
- No, you didn't.

01:16:44.868 --> 01:16:46.803
- So everything's really okay?

01:16:48.337 --> 01:16:51.207
- No, but it will be.

01:16:59.816 --> 01:17:00.817
- Thank you.

01:17:01.851 --> 01:17:02.886
- Yeah.

01:17:03.887 --> 01:17:05.689
Come on, let's go.

01:17:07.757 --> 01:17:09.168
I thought you might
be needing these

01:17:09.192 --> 01:17:10.803
since you ran outta the house
without 'em, all right?

01:17:10.827 --> 01:17:12.261
Come on, let's go.

01:17:18.835 --> 01:17:19.835
- Indy!

01:17:23.172 --> 01:17:24.207
Are you okay?

01:17:26.776 --> 01:17:28.353
- Yeah.

01:17:28.377 --> 01:17:29.377
- Are you really?

01:17:30.379 --> 01:17:33.249
- I'm sorry, I
just thought that.

01:17:35.885 --> 01:17:36.962
I thought wrong.

01:17:36.986 --> 01:17:39.999
- Well, that case worker,
she wants to talk to you

01:17:40.023 --> 01:17:42.835
first thing tomorrow
morning at her office

01:17:42.859 --> 01:17:43.960
if that works for you.

01:17:45.161 --> 01:17:47.439
- I guess, but
what about school?

01:17:47.463 --> 01:17:48.874
- Well, I'll deal
with the principal,

01:17:48.898 --> 01:17:50.142
you don't have to worry
about that right now,

01:17:50.166 --> 01:17:51.334
this is more important.

01:17:53.970 --> 01:17:56.005
- What's gonna happen
after the interview?

01:17:57.841 --> 01:17:59.184
- Well, in a couple of
weeks we'll probably

01:17:59.208 --> 01:18:01.954
have to attend a
hearing on your behalf

01:18:01.978 --> 01:18:03.288
where I'll get a chance
to share my side

01:18:03.312 --> 01:18:05.715
and your case worker
will share her side.

01:18:06.883 --> 01:18:08.293
- And what if we don't win?

01:18:08.317 --> 01:18:10.863
- Oh, don't worry, we will win.

01:18:10.887 --> 01:18:12.364
- But just in case.

01:18:12.388 --> 01:18:14.466
Do I have to go
back with Clarise?

01:18:14.490 --> 01:18:16.926
- No, not again.

01:18:19.262 --> 01:18:22.174
- What's gonna happen
to my aunt and uncle?

01:18:22.198 --> 01:18:23.809
- Honestly that's a
decision a judge

01:18:23.833 --> 01:18:25.878
is gonna have to
make and that is

01:18:25.902 --> 01:18:27.837
not our concern
right now, you are.

01:18:28.972 --> 01:18:30.907
And if you're all
all right with it,

01:18:31.841 --> 01:18:34.077
we'd like to be the
ones to look after you.

01:18:35.511 --> 01:18:37.056
- You already have been.

01:18:37.080 --> 01:18:39.224
- Well, I don't mean
just for the weekend,

01:18:39.248 --> 01:18:40.993
I mean I think we could be your

01:18:41.017 --> 01:18:42.852
foster family if that's okay.

01:18:46.956 --> 01:18:47.957
Bring it in.

01:18:54.898 --> 01:18:55.975
- What are you?

01:18:55.999 --> 01:18:57.843
- Oh, would you just smile.

01:18:57.867 --> 01:18:58.867
- I am.

01:19:03.472 --> 01:19:04.917
She is ruining our lives,

01:19:04.941 --> 01:19:06.952
dragging our names
through the mud.

01:19:06.976 --> 01:19:08.553
- We're gonna stop her.

01:19:08.577 --> 01:19:09.955
- When's our lawyer get here?

01:19:09.979 --> 01:19:10.979
- He's on his way.

01:19:13.950 --> 01:19:15.094
- Oh, that's good, that's good
- Thank you so much.

01:19:15.118 --> 01:19:17.396
- Absolutely.

01:19:17.420 --> 01:19:18.931
- Little brat.

01:19:18.955 --> 01:19:22.434
- Shut your mouth,
someone will hear you.

01:19:22.458 --> 01:19:23.458
- Yes, dear.

01:19:26.062 --> 01:19:27.306
Oh, sweetie.

01:19:27.330 --> 01:19:29.875
- Uh, I'll walk you out.

01:19:29.899 --> 01:19:30.876
Dr. Bailey's waiting over here.

01:19:30.900 --> 01:19:31.901
- It's okay.

01:19:34.904 --> 01:19:36.215
- So, not too bad?

01:19:36.239 --> 01:19:37.582
- It was fine.

01:19:37.606 --> 01:19:38.984
- Good, good.

01:19:39.008 --> 01:19:40.008
Hard part's over.

01:19:41.510 --> 01:19:42.510
- Is it?

01:19:44.347 --> 01:19:46.049
- Well, one of the hard parts.

01:19:47.516 --> 01:19:48.516
How do you feel?

01:19:50.319 --> 01:19:53.990
- Hopeful I guess is
the word, I just...

01:19:58.027 --> 01:19:59.027
- What?

01:20:01.264 --> 01:20:02.407
- I'm nervous.

01:20:02.431 --> 01:20:04.944
- I can understand that.

01:20:04.968 --> 01:20:08.848
You've got a lot of changes going
on in your life right now.

01:20:08.872 --> 01:20:10.506
- But I'm not just
nervous for me,

01:20:12.942 --> 01:20:14.043
I'm nervous for them, too.

01:20:15.912 --> 01:20:17.489
Does that make any sense?

01:20:17.513 --> 01:20:19.224
I mean, I realize that
they didn't treat me

01:20:19.248 --> 01:20:21.994
the way they were
supposed to, but...

01:20:22.018 --> 01:20:23.963
- But you still care for them.

01:20:23.987 --> 01:20:25.464
- Yeah.

01:20:25.488 --> 01:20:27.056
I mean, sort of.

01:20:30.126 --> 01:20:31.570
Is that weird?

01:20:31.594 --> 01:20:34.397
- Bryant was right about
you, you are a unique person

01:20:35.564 --> 01:20:36.832
with a kind heart.

01:20:37.967 --> 01:20:41.947
Whatever it is you're
feeling, it's okay,

01:20:41.971 --> 01:20:44.950
I think the kids have
a movie night planned

01:20:44.974 --> 01:20:47.110
maybe we oughta get home and
see what they've picked.

01:21:02.691 --> 01:21:05.061
- So this is what a movie
night is really like?

01:21:06.930 --> 01:21:07.930
- Yeah.

01:21:09.565 --> 01:21:10.976
- Cool.

01:21:30.386 --> 01:21:32.021
I don't know what
to say to that.

01:21:36.325 --> 01:21:37.136
- What's his number?

01:21:37.160 --> 01:21:38.203
I'll text him.

01:21:38.227 --> 01:21:39.204
- What?

01:21:39.228 --> 01:21:40.228
No.

01:21:40.729 --> 01:21:42.065
What are you gonna say?

01:21:43.967 --> 01:21:44.709
- Don't worry.

01:21:44.733 --> 01:21:45.733
May I?

01:21:46.635 --> 01:21:48.013
- You guys are being too loud.

01:21:48.037 --> 01:21:49.037
- Sorry.

01:21:58.681 --> 01:21:59.681
- Happy?

01:22:01.117 --> 01:22:03.328
- It's better than
what I would've said.

01:22:04.988 --> 01:22:07.132
- Roni, you've seen this movie
at least a hundred times

01:22:07.156 --> 01:22:08.633
do you really need
us to be quiet?

01:22:08.657 --> 01:22:11.236
- Stop talking now, people.

01:22:12.728 --> 01:22:14.197
- It's her favorite part.

01:22:15.664 --> 01:22:19.568
- So this is what a movie
night is really like.

01:22:21.004 --> 01:22:22.181
- Pretty much.

01:22:22.205 --> 01:22:24.640
Popcorn, fighting, and movies
you've seen a hundred times.

01:22:30.213 --> 01:22:31.390
- Hi.

01:22:31.414 --> 01:22:32.724
- Hey, are you okay?

01:22:32.748 --> 01:22:34.226
- Yeah, I'm fine.

01:22:34.250 --> 01:22:35.418
- Bryant said that you...

01:22:37.220 --> 01:22:39.431
He's being serious, wasn't he?

01:22:39.455 --> 01:22:40.665
- Yeah.

01:22:40.689 --> 01:22:42.525
- And when you called
you needed my help.

01:22:44.560 --> 01:22:45.770
- Yeah.

01:22:45.794 --> 01:22:48.540
- Indy, I don't
know what to say.

01:22:48.564 --> 01:22:49.374
I'm an idiot.

01:22:49.398 --> 01:22:51.010
- No, you're not.

01:22:51.034 --> 01:22:53.269
You just had your
own stuff going on.

01:22:54.503 --> 01:22:56.305
Speaking of which,
how's your ankle?

01:22:57.673 --> 01:23:02.278
- It's still sore but the doctor
says it's nothing serious.

01:23:03.446 --> 01:23:05.557
Just have to take
it easy for awhile.

01:23:05.581 --> 01:23:06.581
- I'm glad.

01:23:09.252 --> 01:23:10.353
- Are you really okay?

01:23:11.454 --> 01:23:15.558
- I mean, Bryant's dad is
taking care of my case, so.

01:23:17.260 --> 01:23:18.427
It's getting there.

01:23:20.563 --> 01:23:21.473
- Can I see you?

01:23:21.497 --> 01:23:23.242
Are you gonna be at school or?

01:23:23.266 --> 01:23:27.646
- I think I'm gonna stay home
but take notes for me, okay?

01:23:27.670 --> 01:23:29.081
- Yeah.

01:23:29.105 --> 01:23:31.550
Can I come over after
school just to talk?

01:23:31.574 --> 01:23:32.574
- Sure.

01:23:34.210 --> 01:23:37.156
- Indy, I'm really really...

01:23:37.180 --> 01:23:38.180
- I know.

01:23:39.748 --> 01:23:43.586
- See you tomorrow.

01:23:47.656 --> 01:23:49.401
- Hey, do you have a second?

01:23:49.425 --> 01:23:50.269
- Sure.

01:23:50.293 --> 01:23:51.293
Is everything okay?

01:23:52.461 --> 01:23:57.400
- Well, I've had a few friends
digging into the paperwork

01:23:58.634 --> 01:24:02.738
and apparently your mother had
a $300,000 insurance policy

01:24:04.673 --> 01:24:06.251
that your aunt and uncle took,

01:24:06.275 --> 01:24:08.711
as legal guardians,
to raise you.

01:24:11.180 --> 01:24:12.180
- To raise me?

01:24:15.384 --> 01:24:17.320
And they had all this
money the whole time?

01:24:18.354 --> 01:24:21.233
- Did you see any of it?

01:24:21.257 --> 01:24:22.257
- Never.

01:24:23.159 --> 01:24:24.159
- That's the issue.

01:24:25.194 --> 01:24:28.397
- On top of selling everything,
all my mom's stuff?

01:24:30.333 --> 01:24:31.534
- Unfortunately yes.

01:24:33.336 --> 01:24:35.138
But it's all gonna
come up in court.

01:24:37.540 --> 01:24:39.842
- Why did they see
me as such a burden?

01:24:42.645 --> 01:24:43.645
- I'm sorry.

01:24:46.249 --> 01:24:48.393
On the bright side, you
will likely win all

01:24:48.417 --> 01:24:51.330
of that money back and
then some in court.

01:24:51.354 --> 01:24:53.556
It's not gonna look good
for your aunt and uncle.

01:24:54.623 --> 01:24:55.623
- Thank you.

01:25:02.631 --> 01:25:03.799
- The water looks nice.

01:25:06.935 --> 01:25:08.271
You feeling any better?

01:25:11.474 --> 01:25:13.485
- I always thought they
treated me the way they did

01:25:13.509 --> 01:25:15.278
because I cost them
too much money.

01:25:17.280 --> 01:25:18.747
Now I know that's not the case.

01:25:19.915 --> 01:25:22.261
- It's their loss,
you have nothing

01:25:22.285 --> 01:25:23.452
but goodness in your heart.

01:25:24.887 --> 01:25:27.490
Besides, you didn't deserve
the way they treated you.

01:25:30.826 --> 01:25:33.362
- I don't know if I could
ever face them again

01:25:34.630 --> 01:25:38.133
and I have to see Jayda and
Kaitlyn every day at school.

01:25:39.568 --> 01:25:42.438
- True. But the school
year's almost over.

01:25:44.240 --> 01:25:45.240
It is a big school.

01:25:47.443 --> 01:25:52.215
With the school year almost
being over there's this thing

01:25:54.350 --> 01:25:55.451
that starts with a P.

01:25:57.286 --> 01:25:58.286
- Party?

01:25:59.355 --> 01:26:00.765
- Close.

01:26:00.789 --> 01:26:03.635
Prom.

01:26:03.659 --> 01:26:04.659
- What about it?

01:26:06.962 --> 01:26:07.962
- You should go.

01:26:09.698 --> 01:26:13.245
- Jayda and Kaitlyn have been
preparing for prom for months.

01:26:13.269 --> 01:26:15.747
- Then imagine their
faces when you walk in

01:26:15.771 --> 01:26:17.573
with whatever killer
dress you pick.

01:26:18.974 --> 01:26:20.819
With me.

01:26:20.843 --> 01:26:22.554
- With you?

01:26:22.578 --> 01:26:23.578
- If you'll go with me.

01:26:24.480 --> 01:26:25.480
- But my cousins...

01:26:26.849 --> 01:26:29.885
- Well, I just wanted to
go with you, but hey,

01:26:31.520 --> 01:26:33.822
if you wanna make it a group
date with your cousins, then.

01:26:36.625 --> 01:26:40.405
- Did you really
just ask me to prom?

01:26:40.429 --> 01:26:41.429
- Yeah.

01:26:42.398 --> 01:26:43.398
Yeah, I did.

01:26:44.833 --> 01:26:45.833
- Yes.

01:26:47.570 --> 01:26:48.547
I can go.

01:26:48.571 --> 01:26:51.416
I don't have to do chores,
I'm not grounded,

01:26:51.440 --> 01:26:54.477
I don't have to make dinner for
my cousins or their dates.

01:26:57.780 --> 01:26:59.515
I'd love to.

01:27:02.818 --> 01:27:04.596
Do I have to wear a
dress with heels?

01:27:05.821 --> 01:27:08.367
I'll wear the dress
I just, please,

01:27:08.391 --> 01:27:10.369
don't make me wear heels.

01:27:10.393 --> 01:27:13.329
- I'm a guy, I don't care
what shoes you wear.

01:27:14.963 --> 01:27:19.611
- Hey, Indy, there's a boy
here who wants to talk to you.

01:27:19.635 --> 01:27:20.669
- Ah.

01:27:21.604 --> 01:27:22.638
Maxton.

01:27:36.452 --> 01:27:37.496
- Hi.

01:27:37.520 --> 01:27:39.431
- So new digs, huh?

01:27:39.455 --> 01:27:40.656
This place is cool.

01:27:42.057 --> 01:27:44.002
- The Baileys are
really nice people.

01:27:44.026 --> 01:27:46.695
- Yeah, I can't
compete with that.

01:27:48.364 --> 01:27:49.641
- What are you talking about?

01:27:49.665 --> 01:27:50.699
- Look, you

01:27:53.068 --> 01:27:54.937
you have Bryant now

01:27:56.705 --> 01:28:01.043
and I'm stupid for not
asking you out sooner.

01:28:03.011 --> 01:28:06.915
Look, Indy, spending these
last few years with you was

01:28:08.617 --> 01:28:10.653
really a dream come true for me.

01:28:13.121 --> 01:28:15.458
You made it worth going
to school every day.

01:28:16.725 --> 01:28:17.536
- Really?

01:28:17.560 --> 01:28:19.037
- Yeah.

01:28:19.061 --> 01:28:23.699
I mean, wish I'd done more and
been more of what you needed

01:28:24.633 --> 01:28:27.603
but I didn't know what that was.

01:28:28.737 --> 01:28:30.739
- You were exactly
what I needed.

01:28:32.007 --> 01:28:33.585
You helped me through some of

01:28:33.609 --> 01:28:35.544
the hardest times I've ever had.

01:28:36.645 --> 01:28:39.748
You made me forget how
bad my life really was.

01:28:42.885 --> 01:28:43.795
- Did you really get removed

01:28:43.819 --> 01:28:45.488
from the house because of abuse?

01:28:48.156 --> 01:28:49.156
- Yeah.

01:28:49.892 --> 01:28:52.094
- Did they hurt you?

01:28:54.029 --> 01:28:55.407
Why didn't you tell me?

01:28:55.431 --> 01:28:57.733
I coulda helped, I
coulda done something.

01:28:59.402 --> 01:29:05.450
- My case is more emotional
abuse which I didn't know

01:29:05.474 --> 01:29:07.476
you could take
somebody to court for.

01:29:07.910 --> 01:29:08.910
But I'm safe now.

01:29:10.879 --> 01:29:12.080
Dr. Bailey's helping me.

01:29:13.982 --> 01:29:14.982
- He seems decent.

01:29:16.885 --> 01:29:17.885
I'm happy for you.

01:29:19.087 --> 01:29:21.390
Are you gonna change schools or?

01:29:22.791 --> 01:29:24.936
- I thought about it but since Dr.
Bailey

01:29:24.960 --> 01:29:28.797
works at the school I
figured I better stay.

01:29:29.998 --> 01:29:33.702
- Well, I'm glad you're staying
even if it's not with me.

01:29:35.504 --> 01:29:36.114
- Maxton...

01:29:36.138 --> 01:29:37.749
- Hey, it's okay.

01:29:37.773 --> 01:29:39.451
This is the part where
you tell me you're going

01:29:39.475 --> 01:29:42.478
with the handsome prince
and not the regular dude.

01:29:45.080 --> 01:29:45.957
- I'm sorry.

01:29:45.981 --> 01:29:46.981
- Don't be.

01:29:48.484 --> 01:29:51.463
It might not of been
legit but you were mine

01:29:51.487 --> 01:29:54.022
for years and I don't
need more than that.

01:29:55.991 --> 01:30:00.996
- You deserve more than that
and you'll have it some day.

01:30:05.033 --> 01:30:06.033
- Just not with you.

01:30:08.871 --> 01:30:10.573
- You know what you will have?

01:30:12.140 --> 01:30:15.687
A best friend.

01:30:15.711 --> 01:30:18.847
Promise me that you'll
stay my best friend.

01:30:20.716 --> 01:30:21.716
- Friends for life?

01:30:22.818 --> 01:30:24.463
- Forever.

01:30:35.230 --> 01:30:37.642
- As I watched him walk away

01:30:37.666 --> 01:30:39.811
I fully expected things to
be awkward here and there

01:30:39.835 --> 01:30:42.538
especially if he and Bryant
were in the same room,

01:30:43.739 --> 01:30:47.652
but Maxton has been such a huge
part of my life for so long

01:30:47.676 --> 01:30:49.778
and we were learning now
what love really was.

01:30:50.879 --> 01:30:52.114
I think that'll help us both.

01:30:53.949 --> 01:30:54.949
We'll be fine.

01:30:59.121 --> 01:31:01.666
As luck would have it, Dr.
Bailey wasn't

01:31:01.690 --> 01:31:05.561
just good at his job,
he was really good.

01:31:06.829 --> 01:31:08.973
Between his testimony and
the state's investigation

01:31:08.997 --> 01:31:11.910
my aunt and uncle not
only lost custody of me,

01:31:11.934 --> 01:31:13.645
they were ordered
to make payments

01:31:13.669 --> 01:31:16.180
to pay back my mom's
life insurance policy.

01:31:16.204 --> 01:31:18.182
As well as another
big sum to make up

01:31:18.206 --> 01:31:21.209
for the missing assets and any
emotional trauma they caused.

01:31:23.278 --> 01:31:25.757
I couldn't touch most
of it until I was 18

01:31:25.781 --> 01:31:29.918
but holy smokes, I was loaded.

01:31:31.787 --> 01:31:34.056
The first thing I did was
get a set of wheels.

01:31:35.223 --> 01:31:38.036
Bryant's dad assured
me it was a good deal.

01:31:38.060 --> 01:31:39.771
He also told me it'd be wise not

01:31:39.795 --> 01:31:41.664
to spend all my money at once.

01:31:42.831 --> 01:31:45.568
Funny thing was, I never
cared about the money,

01:31:46.935 --> 01:31:50.973
never even thought I had any,
I only wanted to belong.

01:31:54.777 --> 01:31:57.255
I did move out to the
pool house, though.

01:31:57.279 --> 01:31:59.290
Since Bryant and I were dating

01:31:59.314 --> 01:32:01.283
I figured it was the
right thing to do.

01:32:02.885 --> 01:32:06.831
We all have dreams; some
of us wanna be singers,

01:32:06.855 --> 01:32:08.957
dancers, astronauts, whatever,

01:32:10.893 --> 01:32:13.962
after losing my mom
this was mine.

01:32:15.163 --> 01:32:17.900
To have a family again.

01:32:32.715 --> 01:32:34.859
- Wow.

01:32:34.883 --> 01:32:35.918
- Yeah?

01:32:38.253 --> 01:32:39.631
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, you're not

01:32:39.655 --> 01:32:41.032
doing prom stuff
without me, are ya?

01:32:41.056 --> 01:32:41.866
- Dad!

01:32:41.890 --> 01:32:43.367
You and your pictures.

01:32:43.391 --> 01:32:46.938
- Yeah, you don't go to
prom without pictures.

01:32:46.962 --> 01:32:47.996
And a little...

01:32:50.699 --> 01:32:51.876
Battery issue.

01:32:51.900 --> 01:32:53.035
Hang on just a sec.

01:32:57.840 --> 01:32:59.842
- Do you know how
beautiful you are?

01:33:01.777 --> 01:33:03.646
- For the first time
I feel beautiful

01:33:04.913 --> 01:33:06.615
and that's all because of you.

01:33:07.382 --> 01:33:12.587
- No, not me.

01:33:13.255 --> 01:33:17.860
You've always been this way.

01:33:28.971 --> 01:33:30.939
You know, if it wasn't for Mrs.
Wiggins

01:33:32.307 --> 01:33:34.009
I don't think we'd
be here today.

01:33:35.077 --> 01:33:39.281
So I got you
something, wait here.

01:33:45.921 --> 01:33:47.398
- Oh.

01:33:47.422 --> 01:33:48.957
She's beautiful.

01:33:50.893 --> 01:33:51.893
Thank you.

01:33:55.397 --> 01:33:58.743
This is the happiest
moment of my life.

01:33:58.767 --> 01:33:59.944
- I'm gonna be competing with

01:33:59.968 --> 01:34:02.881
the cat for your
attention, aren't I?

01:34:02.905 --> 01:34:05.984
- She's not the only
reason why I'm happy.

01:34:06.008 --> 01:34:07.886
- Okie doke, problem solved.

01:34:07.910 --> 01:34:08.977
Picture time.

01:34:10.813 --> 01:34:11.756
Oh yeah.

01:34:11.780 --> 01:34:14.158
Oh, Bryant's got two dates.

01:34:14.182 --> 01:34:15.182
And nice.

01:34:18.787 --> 01:34:19.787
Ah, nice.

01:34:20.322 --> 01:34:22.033
Look at that.

01:34:22.057 --> 01:34:24.693
- Roni, get in here.

01:34:27.930 --> 01:34:29.908
- Nice.
- Now you, Dr. Bailey.

01:34:29.932 --> 01:34:31.309
- Oh, okay.

01:34:31.333 --> 01:34:32.667
If you insist.

